dcterms:description: The Vi-Fi multimodal dataset consists of collected and labeled walking data across 98 different sequences over 5 scenes with pedestrians and participants. It contains information across the vision and wireless modalities, including RGB-D data, 9-axis IMU data, and FTM data.
dcterms:title: Vi-Fi multimodal dataset

dcterms:description: RGB-D data collected through a ZED RGB-D camera, used for depth information in the context of multimodal association with WiFi FTM data.
dcterms:title: RGB-D data

dcterms:description: WiFi Fine Time Measurements (FTM) data collected from a user's smartphone device, used for estimating distances in the context of cross-modal association.
dcterms:title: WiFi Fine Time Measurements (FTM)

dcterms:creator: Google
dcterms:description: IMU data collected from Google Pixel smartphones, used in conjunction with other modalities for cross-modal association.
dcterms:title: IMU data

dcterms:title: ViTag
